OL,3,COne year after Assad fall Syria's
OL,4,Cdisplaced children dream of going home
OL,6,FFor many of those within Syria, homes
OL,7,Fgave way to tents in displacement
OL,8,Fcamps, and over time, those camps
OL,9,Fbecame like small towns and cities.
OL,11,FIn the Mahmoudli camp in North-Eastern
OL,12,FSyria, many of the children have only
OL,13,Fever known life in the camp, their
OL,14,Fwhole lives spent in tents, the only
OL,15,Fcontact with their family homes
OL,16,Fthrough the tales told of them.
OL,18,FBritish charity Syrian Refugee Relief
OL,19,FFund runs a school in the camp,
OL,20,Fdesigned to offer a full education to
OL,21,Fthe camp's children.
