OL,3,COne year after Assad fall Syria's
OL,4,Cdisplaced children dream of going home
OL,6,F"The families in the camp care deeply
OL,7,Fabout their children's education."
OL,9,FAt 11, Qadar has big dreams of being a
OL,10,Fdoctor. Since Assad fled Syria, she
OL,11,Fhas dared to believe that one day soon
OL,12,Fshe may yet get to go home. Her
OL,13,Fdrawings tell of the reality and
OL,14,Flonging.
OL,16,F"I draw my school, our tents, and my
OL,17,Fhometown. This is what I see in my
OL,18,Fcountry ` it is mostly destroyed," she
OL,19,Fsays.
