OL,3,COne year after Assad fall Syria's
OL,4,Cdisplaced children dream of going home
OL,6,F"Before the liberation, we had no hope
OL,7,Fof returning, but now we do. We hope
OL,8,Fwe will go back to our town and live
OL,9,Fthere again."
OL,11,FSome of the pupils in the school have
OL,12,Fbegun returning to their family homes,
OL,13,Fbut the joy of return is tempered by
OL,14,Fwhat they find there.
OL,16,FMany returning families have found
OL,17,Ftheir homes badly damaged, and the
OL,18,Fmines littering the land are doing
OL,19,Fdreadful harm.
