OL,3,COne year after Assad fall Syria's
OL,4,Cdisplaced children dream of going home
OL,6,F1400 children have been killed in the
OL,7,F12 months since Assad left, mainly
OL,8,Fbecause they went home unaware of the
OL,9,Fdreadful legacy left behind.
OL,11,FJihad Almahmoud knows his students
OL,12,Fdon't want to stay forever, but he
OL,13,Fwill be there as long as they are.
OL,14,F"The children come to school every
OL,15,Fday, and their eyes are full of hope
OL,16,Ffor a better future, a dignified life,
OL,17,Fand a safe home."
OL,19,FHis great wish is that day comes soon.
